cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning probabilistic first-order logical rules for knowledge base reasoning using a differentiable model. The paper combines neural networks and logical rules to learn the parameters and structure of the rules. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with natural language processing and knowledge representation, which are covered in cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a neural controller system to learn to compose differentiable operations, which falls under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
